nodes.text: Sul Prine's Place was a small home owned by a Human male speeder bike racer named Sul Prine, during the time of the Galactic Civil War. The house was located on the edge of one of Talus' major cities, Dearic. Around 1 ABY, the technology-hating Meatlump criminals damaged several speeder bikes that were parked outside the house. When Vani Korr, a Corellia Times reporter who was investigating the Meatlumps learned of this attack, she tasked a spacer to investigate. The adventurer met Sul Prine at his place and the latter confirmed that the Meatlumps were responsible of the attack. Prine also gave the spacer a Meatlump map he had found. The map allowed the adventurer to eventually find the location of the Meatlump Camps on Talus.

Sul Prine's Place was a location in the 2003 massively multiplayer online role-playing game Star Wars Galaxies, prior to the game's closure on December 15, 2011. Sul Prine's Place was added to the game with the update dubbed "Chapter 10: The Search for the Meatlump King", released on June 19, 2008.
